{"key":"processedPost-18541751","value":{"id":18541751,"first":18541004,"last":18555735,"when":1373517204,"utime":"07/11/13 07:33 AM","content":"Adult-stage fungus gnats don't eat.&nbsp; Their only purpose is to lay eggs which hatch into larvae.&nbsp; They're easy to kill with 2% hydrogen peroxide.&nbsp; If you're in the US, use the peroxide in a brown bottle and dilute it by 1/3 with tap water and pour into where the larvae are feeding.&nbsp; If you ruffle the soil on your houseplants you'll find the source when you see the gnats fly out.&nbsp; Once you do, scrape the soil off the top and water the rest real well with peroxide as described above to kill the larvae.<br />RR","title":"Re: Fungus Gnats in Monotub - Will this work?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}